    "The integrative approach in Starfysh is formulated with a deep variational information bottleneck 26.",
    "The original H&E images are first normalized to [0, 1] per channel.",
    "The alignment between H&E images and ST spot i produces the histology image patches y i ∈ ℝ P×P×C (with P as the side length of the patch and C as the number of image channels, for example, C = 3 for RGB images and C = 1 for grayscale images).",
    "We set P = 26 by default to approximate the number of pixels surrounding each spot.",
    "The image patch y i is then flattened in the Starfysh model and assumed to be generated from the same latent variable z i that informs gene expression (Fig. 1c and Supplementary Fig."
